commentBody:
@Dan 
Rubber Duckie you're the one
Who makes crosswords lots of fun!

@Steve L
Count me as awfully fond of RUBBER duckies, (because they belong in the bath it still qualifies as a squeaky clean theme set)!
(Otherwise, I think it might have been rather dry…)

@Steve L 
In the distance, Steve glimpsed a mob waving pitchforks and torches....


Emus led the parade...

@Liz B 
I also had ALT for HGT, eventually it became clear the answer had to be an alternative way of referring to 'elev'.
I enjoyed this puzzle quite a bit!  It now just dawned on me, as I'd thought earlier, "I've never heard of the 'rubber' breed," it is the TOY duck!

@Once a Marine 
I found this funny as well and was compelled to verify it at <a href="https://www.tsa.gov/travel/security-screening/whatcanibring/all-list" target="_blank">https://www.tsa.gov/travel/security-screening/whatcanibring/all-list</a> 

Apparently a bowling pin is considered so club-like as to be a weapon!

@EGW 
Humans can turn practically anything into a weapon. See the "dawn of man" sequence of the movie "2001: A Space Odyssey" for an example.

Now I will check the TSA website to see whether I can pack a femur in my carry-on bag ...

@Gus 

HGT has been in puzzles before. I don’t like it much myself, but it is the abbreviation on my driver’s license. Like some other people, I put ALT first. 

And on the other hand, I live on Travis Hts. Blvd.

@Gus 

I always have to at my license to see how they abbreviate “height.”

Good luck with your crossword solving! And have fun!

@Eric Hougland -- Me too!

@Vaer -- Would you believe that I could have gotten it in 2, but chose START as my 2nd guess?:)

(I always start with SLATE.  The bot loves it and who am I to argue with the bot?  It was very lucky this time.)

@Confused 

It's the actor's last name who portrayed Master Kahn in Kung Fu. Philip is his first name. 

<a href="https://kung-fu.fandom.com/wiki/Philip_Ahn" target="_blank">https://kung-fu.fandom.com/wiki/Philip_Ahn</a>

@Confused 

<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philip_Ahn" target="_blank">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philip_Ahn</a>

